    "biography": "<p>Highly magical, free-willed, intelligent beings from the elemental plane of air. Tall humanoids wreathed in clouds.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mundane damage immunity:</strong> Can only be harmed by magical attacks.</li>\n<li><strong>Magic powers: </strong>Each can be used three times per day:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Whirlwind form:</strong> 5 rounds to transform (or change back). 70&rsquo; tall, 20&rsquo; wide at top, 10&rsquo; wide at base. Moves at 120&rsquo; (40&rsquo;). 2d6 damage to all in path. Creatures with less than 2HD swept aside (Physical save).</li>\n<li><strong>Gaseous form</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Invisibility</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Illusion: </strong>Visual and audial. No concentration required. Remains until touched or dispelled.</li>\n<li><strong>Create food and drink: </strong>For 12 humans and mounts for one day.</li>\n<li><strong>Conjure metallic objects:</strong> Up to 10 encumbrance in weight. Temporary: hardness determines duration (gold: 1 day; iron: 1 round).</li>\n<li><strong>Conjure soft goods / wooden objects:</strong> Up to 10 encumbrance in weight. Permanent.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Carrying capacity:</strong> 60 encumbrance without fatigue. Up to 120 encumbrance for 3 turns walking / 1 turn flying. Must rest 1 turn afterwards.</p>\n<p><strong>If killed: </strong>Returns to the plane of air.</p>"
  },
